// Service Mesh Implementation - Sidecar Pattern
// Istio with Envoy Proxy Injection

// ==================== EXTERNAL CLIENTS ====================
External Traffic [icon: aws-api-gateway]

// ==================== SINGLE POD (CLOSE-UP) ====================
Catalog API Pod [icon: k8s-pod, color: green] {
  
  // Envoy Sidecar Proxy (Injected by Istio)
  Envoy Proxy [icon: istio, color: orange]

  // Application Container
  Catalog API [icon: dotnet, color: blue]
}

// ==================== ANOTHER POD ====================
Basket API Pod [icon: k8s-pod, color: green] {
  Envoy Proxy 2 [icon: istio, color: orange]
  Basket API [icon: dotnet, color: blue]
}

// ==================== ISTIO CONTROL PLANE ====================
Istio Control Plane [icon: istio, color: purple] {
  istiod [icon: k8s-control-plane]
}

// ==================== TRAFFIC FLOW ====================

// Inbound: External → Sidecar → App
External Traffic > Envoy Proxy : 1. Inbound Request
Envoy Proxy > Catalog API : 2. Forward to App (localhost)

// Outbound: App → Sidecar → Other Pod's Sidecar → Other App
Catalog API > Envoy Proxy : 3. Outbound Request
Envoy Proxy > Envoy Proxy 2 : 4. mTLS Encrypted
Envoy Proxy 2 > Basket API : 5. Forward to App

// Control Plane Configuration
istiod > Envoy Proxy : Push Config
istiod > Envoy Proxy 2 : Push Config
